WEBVTT

00:02.460 --> 00:03.830
Previously on
"Marvel's Inhumans"...

00:03.830 --> 00:05.330
Find Black Bolt and the rest
of the Royal Family,

00:05.330 --> 00:07.330
and finish your mission.

00:07.330 --> 00:09.380
Declan: You may not be able
to regenerate yourself forever.

00:09.380 --> 00:11.380
One day, you'll die,
and that's it.

00:11.380 --> 00:13.580
I thought being on Earth
would be horrible,

00:13.580 --> 00:14.960
but it's...
Great?

00:14.960 --> 00:16.000
Yeah.

00:17.790 --> 00:19.040
How do you know Maximus?

00:19.040 --> 00:20.170
He paid
for all this research.

00:20.170 --> 00:23.250
He'll kill us all!
Gorgon: No!

00:23.250 --> 00:29.120
[ Rumbling ]

00:29.120 --> 00:30.670
He's gone.
Gorgon's dead.

00:30.670 --> 00:35.830
♪♪

00:43.170 --> 00:44.790
Flora: They're still
coming after us!

00:44.790 --> 00:46.620
Declan: Go! Go!
We're not giving up!

00:46.620 --> 00:48.500
We had nothing
to do with this!

00:48.500 --> 00:51.000
Keep running,
or I'll kill you right now!

00:51.000 --> 00:52.500
[ Indistinct shouting ]

00:52.500 --> 00:54.420
Medusa: They're headed
for the road!
Karnak: Exactly!

00:54.420 --> 00:56.960
That's where
we'll cut them off.

00:56.960 --> 00:58.170
Flora,
to the right!

00:58.170 --> 00:59.750
[ Indistinct shouting ]
Go!

00:59.750 --> 01:01.460
Move, or he's
gonna catch us!

01:01.460 --> 01:03.290
Bolt, to the left!
We'll bring them to you.

01:03.290 --> 01:04.880
Come on!
We got to keep moving!

01:04.880 --> 01:07.120
[ Lockjaw barking ]

01:07.120 --> 01:08.880
[ Indistinct shouting ]

01:11.920 --> 01:13.210
[ Grunts ]

01:13.210 --> 01:14.580
Wait, wait, wait!

01:14.580 --> 01:16.710
I suggest you stop,

01:16.710 --> 01:19.620
unless you want
to deal with my husband.

01:19.620 --> 01:21.500
♪♪

01:21.500 --> 01:23.380
[ Lockjaw barks ]

01:23.380 --> 01:25.670
I'm a scientist.
I-I'm not a soldier.

01:25.670 --> 01:27.040
You're a collaborator --

01:27.040 --> 01:29.460
with the people responsible
for my cousin's death.

01:29.460 --> 01:31.420
Collaborator?
Y-You freed me, remember?!

01:31.420 --> 01:34.120
That woman, she --
she murdered my assistant!

01:34.120 --> 01:35.670
What were you doing
with Maximus?

01:35.670 --> 01:37.920
Why is he
so interested?
W-We've never even met.

01:37.920 --> 01:40.120
He's funding my research

01:40.120 --> 01:41.460
for how people on Earth
are transforming,

01:41.460 --> 01:42.880
the -- the --
the process behind it,

01:42.880 --> 01:44.540
how it
can be replicated.

01:44.540 --> 01:46.620
Look, I've got all my research.
It's in my --

01:46.620 --> 01:48.170
It's in my briefcase,
but --

01:48.170 --> 01:50.500
This is why Maximus
led the coup against us.

01:50.500 --> 01:52.500
He wants to go through
Terrigenesis again,

01:52.500 --> 01:54.380
and he knew
we would stop him.

01:54.380 --> 01:56.040
The Genetic Council wouldn't
allow something like this,

01:56.040 --> 01:57.080
even if
we weren't there.

01:57.080 --> 01:59.080
♪♪

01:59.080 --> 02:00.920
Unless they've already
been murdered.

02:00.920 --> 02:02.380
♪♪

02:02.380 --> 02:04.420
How many more
have to die?

02:04.420 --> 02:10.120
♪♪

02:12.880 --> 02:22.880
♪♪

02:22.880 --> 02:29.670
♪♪

02:29.670 --> 02:39.290
♪♪

02:39.290 --> 02:49.250
♪♪

02:49.250 --> 02:51.580
What do you
want to do now?

02:51.580 --> 02:56.000
♪♪

02:56.000 --> 02:59.540
What kind of message
do you want to send to Maximus?

02:59.540 --> 03:08.120
♪♪

03:08.120 --> 03:09.620
You brought this
on yourself.

03:09.620 --> 03:10.880
No. No!

03:10.880 --> 03:12.210
[ Bones crack ]
[ Groans ]

03:12.210 --> 03:15.210
[ Body thuds ]

03:15.210 --> 03:16.790
Why?

03:16.790 --> 03:20.250
She'll come back.
She always does.

03:20.250 --> 03:22.380
Let's hope not.

03:22.380 --> 03:24.380
Sending her body
will get Maximus' attention.

03:24.380 --> 03:27.960
The losses will be severe
if he continues.

03:27.960 --> 03:30.080
This has to stop!

03:30.080 --> 03:33.540
We cannot go around
killing everyone.

03:33.540 --> 03:36.880
Remember what
you represent.

03:36.880 --> 03:38.080
What kind of king
would you be

03:38.080 --> 03:39.620
if you killed
your own brother?

03:39.620 --> 03:41.380
What kind of kingdom
would Attilan be

03:41.380 --> 03:43.380
if you descended
to that level?

03:43.380 --> 03:46.710
There will be no kingdom
unless we act!

03:46.710 --> 03:49.500
Actions
have consequences.

03:49.500 --> 03:51.710
That's a lesson
Maximus is about to learn.

03:51.710 --> 04:00.920
♪♪

04:00.920 --> 04:02.580
Maximus:
I'd have to be a fool

04:02.580 --> 04:04.250
to think that Tibor
and his group

04:04.250 --> 04:07.170
were the only ones who were part
of the rebel uprising.

04:07.170 --> 04:08.540
Begin a search.

04:08.540 --> 04:12.000
♪♪

04:12.000 --> 04:13.210
[ Grunts ]

04:13.210 --> 04:14.500
Don't move!

04:14.500 --> 04:16.330
Crystal:
Don't even try.

04:16.330 --> 04:18.210
I'll fry those guns
right out of your hands.

04:18.210 --> 04:22.250
[ Lockjaw growls ]

04:22.250 --> 04:24.620
Seems your time on Earth
has emboldened you.

04:24.620 --> 04:26.920
I have a message
from your king.

04:26.920 --> 04:29.380
Black Bolt asserts the right
to call for parley.

04:29.380 --> 04:30.960
Under the rules
preserved by our people,

04:30.960 --> 04:32.580
you must abide.

04:32.580 --> 04:34.670
We return your team
as an act of good faith.

04:34.670 --> 04:37.120
♪♪

04:37.120 --> 04:40.170
Why now?

04:40.170 --> 04:47.290
♪♪

04:47.290 --> 04:49.580
Gorgon is dead.

04:49.580 --> 04:53.040
♪♪

04:53.040 --> 04:55.380
At least
I understand.

04:55.380 --> 04:57.750
You have had enough.

04:57.750 --> 04:59.830
Request granted.

04:59.830 --> 05:02.670
We'll meet at midday.

05:02.670 --> 05:04.620
♪♪

05:04.620 --> 05:05.960
We could've taken her.
No.

05:05.960 --> 05:07.580
Besides...

05:07.580 --> 05:10.580
I'm getting
what I want.

05:10.580 --> 05:16.040
For the first time in my life,
my family has come to me,

05:16.040 --> 05:19.670
and I'll have the advantage
once they're all together.

05:19.670 --> 05:21.670
♪♪

05:21.670 --> 05:25.670
[ Chuckles ]

05:25.670 --> 05:28.210
Midday.

05:28.210 --> 05:30.880
Perfect time
for his execution.

05:30.880 --> 05:34.000
Karnak,
that can't be our intent.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.000
A parley is diplomacy.

05:36.000 --> 05:38.080
It's to avoid
more bloodshed.

05:38.080 --> 05:40.250
A stalling tactic,
at best.

05:40.250 --> 05:42.790
He thinks we're weak,
exhausted,

05:42.790 --> 05:44.920
and he wants
to take advantage of that.

05:44.920 --> 05:46.380
And what if
we are?

05:46.380 --> 05:49.670
Not weak, but tired.

05:49.670 --> 05:52.250
This family has been marked
by so much loss.

05:52.250 --> 05:54.210
I can feel this
tearing us apart.

05:57.670 --> 05:58.880
Survive?

06:00.120 --> 06:03.710
I want to do more
than survive.

06:05.000 --> 06:08.040
Is this the life
that you wanted?

06:08.040 --> 06:14.290
♪♪

06:14.290 --> 06:18.000
I understand that
you have to deal with reality,

06:18.000 --> 06:20.000
and I know
that Maximus sent assassins.

06:20.000 --> 06:21.170
But where
does this end?

06:21.170 --> 06:27.290
♪♪

06:27.290 --> 06:28.540
And what if
the parley doesn't work?

06:28.540 --> 06:38.460
♪♪

06:38.460 --> 06:43.620
I understand more than most
what Maximus is capable of.

06:43.620 --> 06:48.380
And I know he has to pay
for his actions, but...

06:48.380 --> 06:50.670
please...

06:50.670 --> 06:52.710
please...

06:52.710 --> 07:02.170
♪♪

07:02.170 --> 07:04.790
♪♪

07:04.790 --> 07:09.380
One more
place to go.

07:09.380 --> 07:12.960
All of us.

07:12.960 --> 07:19.920
♪♪

07:19.920 --> 07:24.040
[ Lockjaw grunts ]

07:24.040 --> 07:27.790
[ Lockjaw panting ]

07:27.790 --> 07:35.000
♪♪

07:35.000 --> 07:37.920
[ Lockjaw howls ]

07:37.920 --> 07:40.670
Wait.

07:40.670 --> 07:44.170
[ Howling continues ]

07:44.170 --> 07:53.040
♪♪

07:53.040 --> 07:55.620
♪♪

07:55.620 --> 07:56.750
Crystal: Triton!

07:56.750 --> 08:05.040
♪♪

08:05.040 --> 08:08.080
♪♪

08:13.170 --> 08:14.250
[ Lockjaw grunts ]

08:14.250 --> 08:17.210
♪♪

08:17.210 --> 08:19.540
We thought
you were dead.

08:19.540 --> 08:21.380
I was wounded
in the attack,

08:21.380 --> 08:23.790
but we set a meeting place
in advance,

08:23.790 --> 08:25.330
should anything
go wrong.

08:25.330 --> 08:27.040
Our king felt it best
that Maximus believe

08:27.040 --> 08:28.040
that his plan
was working.

08:28.040 --> 08:29.710
♪♪

08:29.710 --> 08:32.120
Crystal: Why were we kept
in the dark?

08:32.120 --> 08:33.920
I'm sure
he had his reasons.

08:33.920 --> 08:35.880
Medusa:
Yes, well...

08:35.880 --> 08:37.960
♪♪

08:37.960 --> 08:38.920
Triton:
Where's Gorgon?

08:38.920 --> 08:41.710
Come here.

08:41.710 --> 08:43.290
♪♪

08:43.290 --> 08:45.040
He's dead.

08:45.040 --> 08:47.620
♪♪

08:47.620 --> 08:50.040
And his death is real.
It was not part of some plan...

08:50.040 --> 08:53.670
secret or otherwise.

08:53.670 --> 08:57.120
♪♪

08:57.120 --> 08:58.620
Where?

08:58.620 --> 09:00.210
Home.

09:00.210 --> 09:04.080
♪♪

09:04.080 --> 09:06.880
To the Royal Bunker.

09:06.880 --> 09:09.920
♪♪

09:09.920 --> 09:11.960
So,
this is our bunker?

09:11.960 --> 09:13.790
♪♪

09:13.790 --> 09:16.000
Why have I never
seen this before?

09:16.000 --> 09:18.750
♪♪

09:18.750 --> 09:19.670
Why do
we have this?

09:19.670 --> 09:23.000
♪♪

09:23.000 --> 09:25.620
In preparation
for moments like this.

09:25.620 --> 09:27.290
♪♪

09:27.290 --> 09:29.330
How far away are we
from the palace?

09:29.330 --> 09:31.120
Excuse me.
Where are we?

09:31.120 --> 09:32.750
Attilan.
We're on the Moon now.

09:32.750 --> 09:33.880
[ Laughs ]

09:33.880 --> 09:35.790
Come on.

09:35.790 --> 09:37.210
[ Chuckles ] Please.

09:37.210 --> 09:39.750
♪♪

09:39.750 --> 09:42.880
Okay, fish guy,
teleporting dog, yeah.

09:42.880 --> 09:44.170
Okay, maybe.

09:44.170 --> 09:46.080
Are you having trouble
keeping up?

09:46.080 --> 09:47.380
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

09:47.380 --> 09:48.750
Yeah, me, too.

09:48.750 --> 09:50.540
Triton is alive.

09:50.540 --> 09:52.120
We have
a secret bunker

09:52.120 --> 09:55.790
and a strategy
that has been long in the works.

09:55.790 --> 09:58.170
Maybe Gorgon's death,
maybe this --

09:58.170 --> 09:59.540
this was all
a part of your plan?

10:05.580 --> 10:07.210
♪♪

10:07.210 --> 10:09.000
As someone
who was once married,

10:09.000 --> 10:10.210
that looks
very familiar.

10:10.210 --> 10:12.210
It might be wise
at this moment

10:12.210 --> 10:13.880
for you
to take a vow of silence.

10:13.880 --> 10:21.620
♪♪

10:21.620 --> 10:23.790
You allowed us all
to mourn Triton's death.

10:23.790 --> 10:26.330
You deny us our dignity
when you lie.

10:26.330 --> 10:30.750
♪♪

10:30.750 --> 10:33.000
But it is your duty
as my husband

10:33.000 --> 10:34.920
to be honest to me
in all things,

10:34.920 --> 10:36.290
to make me
your partner.

10:36.290 --> 10:38.580
When you make a decision
like this,

10:38.580 --> 10:41.750
when you sideline me,
it is insulting.

10:41.750 --> 10:43.380
♪♪

10:43.380 --> 10:46.170
This time away,
on Earth, it...

10:46.170 --> 10:49.830
it allowed me to step back
and take a look at things,

10:49.830 --> 10:53.500
to see how people
perceived me -- us.

10:53.500 --> 10:57.540
And I love you,
and that has never changed.

10:57.540 --> 11:00.290
But I am not going to
just be your interpreter.

11:00.290 --> 11:02.000
I need
to have a say

11:02.000 --> 11:05.040
in -- in the things that affect
our people, our lives.

11:05.040 --> 11:06.750
I am the queen,

11:06.750 --> 11:10.000
and we move together
or not at all.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.620
♪♪

11:11.620 --> 11:14.880
Now, tell me,
what is the plan?

11:14.880 --> 11:20.790
♪♪

11:20.790 --> 11:23.290
Preparing for war.

11:23.290 --> 11:30.210
♪♪

11:30.210 --> 11:32.250
Where's he going?

11:32.250 --> 11:35.000
♪♪

11:35.000 --> 11:37.830
To undermine
an imposter.

11:37.830 --> 11:43.000
♪♪

11:53.250 --> 11:55.210
There you are.

11:55.210 --> 11:59.000
I was beginning to wonder
how long I'd have to wait.

11:59.000 --> 12:00.920
[ Sighs ]

12:00.920 --> 12:02.500
They sent me back.

12:03.790 --> 12:06.080
They're looking
to bargain.

12:06.080 --> 12:08.170
They've run out
of choices.

12:08.170 --> 12:09.830
I'm certain
Gorgon's death

12:09.830 --> 12:12.420
is what motivated
Black Bolt's offer of parley.

12:13.710 --> 12:15.620
We have all
suffered losses.

12:15.620 --> 12:17.120
Indeed.

12:17.120 --> 12:19.670
And that's why it's important
for me to acknowledge that,

12:19.670 --> 12:21.670
even though
he was a traitor.

12:21.670 --> 12:23.210
The people
need to see me

12:23.210 --> 12:25.000
honor the death
of a family member.

12:25.000 --> 12:27.830
I'll take the high road,
as a king must.

12:30.880 --> 12:33.460
Is something wrong?

12:33.460 --> 12:35.080
♪♪

12:35.080 --> 12:37.420
You want
to become Inhuman.

12:37.420 --> 12:40.380
That's your motivation
behind this revolt.

12:40.380 --> 12:43.250
Why do you care
about my motivation

12:43.250 --> 12:45.670
if it gets you
what you want?

12:45.670 --> 12:47.670
♪♪

12:47.670 --> 12:52.120
Because the reason
I followed you is because I...

12:52.120 --> 12:56.290
saw someone who,
even though he was simply human,

12:56.290 --> 12:59.960
overcame that
and became king.

12:59.960 --> 13:02.380
That was someone
I could admire.

13:02.380 --> 13:04.380
♪♪

13:04.380 --> 13:08.670
So I'm really good...

13:08.670 --> 13:10.790
for a human.

13:10.790 --> 13:14.210
Is that the story
you fell in love with?

13:14.210 --> 13:15.830
That wasn't --
But it is.

13:15.830 --> 13:17.170
You see...

13:17.170 --> 13:20.580
everywhere I go,
no matter what I do,

13:20.580 --> 13:22.330
that'll always be
the story.

13:22.330 --> 13:25.500
"He did so well,
given what he is."

13:25.500 --> 13:29.250
Something less than,
something to be pitied.

13:29.250 --> 13:30.880
♪♪

13:30.880 --> 13:33.670
But not anymore.

13:33.670 --> 13:35.620
I've almost got
everything that I need

13:35.620 --> 13:38.080
to become
the most powerful Inhuman ever.

13:38.080 --> 13:40.420
And once I've been through
Terrigenesis again,

13:40.420 --> 13:43.460
I'm going to lead Attilan
to a new era.

13:43.460 --> 13:46.380
The people need to see
what I represent,

13:46.380 --> 13:49.000
that they can go from the least
to the greatest.

13:49.000 --> 13:51.120
That's the new story
of Maximus,

13:51.120 --> 13:53.210
and it can be their story,
as well.

13:53.210 --> 13:56.420
One that
takes us to Earth

13:56.420 --> 14:00.080
and to a life
far larger than...

14:00.080 --> 14:02.620
they ever imagined.

14:02.620 --> 14:07.460
♪♪

14:07.460 --> 14:10.790
So, the, um,
the research is controversial,

14:10.790 --> 14:13.670
to say the least,
and complex, you know.

14:13.670 --> 14:15.790
Really, I should just
simplify it for you.

14:15.790 --> 14:18.120
I'll try my best
to follow.

14:19.170 --> 14:20.920
Okay.

14:20.920 --> 14:25.170
So, Maximus wants to splice
his DNA with these samples,

14:25.170 --> 14:27.210
and then he promised
to show me a process

14:27.210 --> 14:28.920
that would create
some kind of transformation.

14:28.920 --> 14:32.750
It's called Terrigenesis.

14:32.750 --> 14:34.330
Okay.

14:34.330 --> 14:35.920
So...

14:35.920 --> 14:37.170
is that
why I'm here?

14:37.170 --> 14:38.540
Um...

14:38.540 --> 14:40.330
'Cause I don't really
have anything to contribute

14:40.330 --> 14:41.330
to a war.

14:41.330 --> 14:43.250
If Black Bolt
brought you,

14:43.250 --> 14:45.120
then you have
some value.

14:45.120 --> 14:47.210
Okay, but...

14:47.210 --> 14:48.920
I'll be safe here,
right?

14:48.920 --> 14:50.120
In this bunker?

14:50.120 --> 14:54.210
♪♪

14:54.210 --> 14:56.210
None of us are safe.

14:56.210 --> 15:05.710
♪♪

15:05.710 --> 15:12.330
♪♪

15:12.330 --> 15:15.000
People of Attilan...

15:15.000 --> 15:16.830
friends...

15:16.830 --> 15:23.830
we are here to honor the former
captain of Royal Guard,

15:23.830 --> 15:26.960
my beloved cousin Gorgon.

15:26.960 --> 15:28.580
♪♪

15:28.580 --> 15:31.170
These are complicated times.

15:31.170 --> 15:35.000
And the death of a family member
can only bring me grief.

15:35.000 --> 15:38.000
My heart aches...

15:38.000 --> 15:42.040
because Gorgon and I
can never find a way

15:42.040 --> 15:43.920
to bridge our differences.

15:43.920 --> 15:45.540
♪♪

15:45.540 --> 15:48.120
We spent a childhood together.

15:48.120 --> 15:54.170
We grew strong together,
side by side, and yet...

15:54.170 --> 15:58.750
there was always a distance.

15:58.750 --> 16:01.290
I did my best.

16:01.290 --> 16:03.120
♪♪

16:03.120 --> 16:05.880
I only wish
he'd put forth the same effort.

16:05.880 --> 16:10.080
There it was, a chasm.

16:10.080 --> 16:13.540
He could never see me
for who I truly am.

16:13.540 --> 16:17.380
That seems to be the tragedy
of my entire family --

16:17.380 --> 16:21.620
a blindness
that poisons everything.

16:21.620 --> 16:23.620
They couldn't see me.

16:23.620 --> 16:25.500
They couldn't see you.

16:25.500 --> 16:26.540
And now...

16:26.540 --> 16:27.540
♪♪

16:27.540 --> 16:29.460
...we are all paying the price.

16:29.460 --> 16:32.290
♪♪

16:32.290 --> 16:36.080
We are about to enter
into the field for parley,

16:36.080 --> 16:40.380
and my deepest wish is for us
to set aside our differences

16:40.380 --> 16:43.170
and to avoid any more loss.

16:43.170 --> 16:45.380
♪♪

16:45.380 --> 16:49.960
May our dear Gorgon
be the last to fall.

16:49.960 --> 16:59.960
♪♪

16:59.960 --> 17:08.920
♪♪

17:08.920 --> 17:11.790
You'll meet Black Bolt
at the center.

17:11.790 --> 17:13.960
No weapons,
only discussion.

17:13.960 --> 17:15.500
He is
to make his offer,

17:15.500 --> 17:17.210
and then it is up to you
to accept or deny.

17:17.210 --> 17:18.540
No blood
is to be shed --

17:18.540 --> 17:22.580
Right. Yes.

17:22.580 --> 17:25.750
[ Sighs ]

17:25.750 --> 17:28.960
♪♪

17:28.960 --> 17:30.170
[ Spectators murmuring ]

17:30.170 --> 17:33.080
There he is.

17:33.080 --> 17:35.040
[ Chuckling ]
And he has my scientist.

17:35.040 --> 17:36.540
Crystal:
I hate him.

17:36.540 --> 17:37.920
And it looks like
we've come crawling.

17:37.920 --> 17:47.750
♪♪

17:47.750 --> 17:57.580
♪♪

17:57.580 --> 18:03.580
♪♪

18:03.580 --> 18:05.710
Not the reunion
I hoped for, brother.

18:05.710 --> 18:07.540
We could've
done this privately.

18:07.540 --> 18:08.750
Where's the fun
in that?

18:08.750 --> 18:10.460
You are family,

18:10.460 --> 18:13.420
and because of that,
we're here to extend grace.

18:13.420 --> 18:15.080
♪♪

18:15.080 --> 18:17.420
You insist
on a second Terrigenesis,

18:17.420 --> 18:20.580
so we are going to
grant you that request.

18:20.580 --> 18:24.170
We're willing to turn over
your human scientist

18:24.170 --> 18:26.210
so that
you can proceed.

18:26.210 --> 18:29.830
But in return,
we reclaim our throne,

18:29.830 --> 18:31.500
which is
rightfully ours.

18:31.500 --> 18:34.330
We will set aside
any punishment

18:34.330 --> 18:37.210
so that Attilan
can return to peace.

18:37.210 --> 18:38.750
You want
to become one of us?

18:38.750 --> 18:41.420
♪♪

18:41.420 --> 18:43.670
We want that, too.

18:43.670 --> 18:50.790
♪♪

18:50.790 --> 18:53.000
I accept.

18:53.000 --> 18:57.620
[ Spectators murmuring ]

18:57.620 --> 19:06.670
♪♪

19:06.670 --> 19:15.290
♪♪

19:15.290 --> 19:17.710
Black Bolt,
is this right?

19:17.710 --> 19:20.750
Exchanging a human
for our benefit?

19:20.750 --> 19:23.040
Dissension in
the family.

19:23.040 --> 19:24.670
Say it isn't so.

19:24.670 --> 19:26.710
♪♪

19:26.710 --> 19:28.460
But not
entirely unexpected.

19:28.460 --> 19:32.290
'Cause now
you have nothing.

19:32.290 --> 19:34.250
It's all mine,

19:34.250 --> 19:36.790
and you hate that,
don't you?

19:36.790 --> 19:39.330
♪♪

19:39.330 --> 19:42.500
Maximus,
I am warning --
Warn me?

19:42.500 --> 19:45.040
You are in no position
to do anything.

19:45.040 --> 19:47.710
Extend grace?
Become one of you?

19:47.710 --> 19:50.540
I have always
been one of you,

19:50.540 --> 19:52.460
and now
I am king!

19:52.460 --> 19:54.000
And will remain so.

19:54.000 --> 19:55.460
You accepted.

19:55.460 --> 19:58.040
I rescued someone
you took prisoner.

19:58.040 --> 19:59.500
He is
a friend of mine,

19:59.500 --> 20:02.080
and I would do anything
for my friends.

20:02.080 --> 20:03.670
I decline
your offer.

20:03.670 --> 20:07.620
♪♪

20:07.620 --> 20:11.750
Don't forget, brother,
this is a parley.

20:11.750 --> 20:14.790
The people of Attilan
would be truly appalled

20:14.790 --> 20:17.540
if you were to use it as
an opportunity to inflict harm.

20:17.540 --> 20:22.080
♪♪

20:22.080 --> 20:25.250
The next time
I see you, brother...

20:25.250 --> 20:26.880
♪♪

20:26.880 --> 20:30.750
...I am
going to kill you.

20:30.750 --> 20:34.580
[ Chuckles ]

20:34.580 --> 20:44.080
♪♪

20:44.080 --> 20:53.670
♪♪

20:53.670 --> 20:56.120
♪♪

21:00.750 --> 21:10.540
♪♪

21:10.540 --> 21:11.540
♪♪

21:11.540 --> 21:13.960
[ Chuckles ]

21:13.960 --> 21:16.420
[ Chuckles ]

21:16.420 --> 21:18.460
What you've done here
is incredible.

21:18.460 --> 21:21.040
Terraforming an entire city
on the Moon,

21:21.040 --> 21:23.580
it's -- [Chuckles]
it's mind-boggling.

21:23.580 --> 21:25.250
Yes, yes.

21:25.250 --> 21:27.880
I was hoping
you could show me your work.

21:27.880 --> 21:30.830
Oh, yes. Um...

21:30.830 --> 21:33.540
Yes, uh...

21:33.540 --> 21:37.210
Each of these DNA samples
came from human beings

21:37.210 --> 21:38.420
who have recently
undergone the transformation

21:38.420 --> 21:41.420
that you call...
Terrigenesis.

21:41.420 --> 21:43.330
And you have a list
of all the powers generated?

21:43.330 --> 21:44.670
Yes.

21:44.670 --> 21:46.790
I want the list,
and I'm going to choose.

21:46.790 --> 21:47.960
Choose?

21:47.960 --> 21:49.540
Which powers I want.

21:49.540 --> 21:51.120
And then we'll do
the gene splice, and --

21:51.120 --> 21:53.120
Yeah, just...
it's not that easy.

21:53.120 --> 21:54.210
Here on Attilan,
it is.

21:54.210 --> 21:55.620
I'm sorry.

21:55.620 --> 21:58.120
You're gonna have to
give me a moment. Um...

21:58.120 --> 22:00.210
I mean, I've got some --
some concerns --

22:00.210 --> 22:01.290
And I don't care.

22:01.290 --> 22:03.000
What you're asking me
to do --

22:03.000 --> 22:04.500
I don't even know
if it's safe.

22:04.500 --> 22:06.790
I mean,
just the genetic piece

22:06.790 --> 22:10.830
requires testing
in a controlled environment.

22:10.830 --> 22:13.790
You want to bypass all that?
That could kill you.

22:13.790 --> 22:15.420
Not to mention that

22:15.420 --> 22:18.710
I don't even know
what Terrigenesis is.

22:20.380 --> 22:24.420
Terrigenesis is
what binds us together

22:24.420 --> 22:27.500
and defines us
as Inhumans.

22:27.500 --> 22:31.210
It unites us across
generations and class,

22:31.210 --> 22:34.000
ties us to our heritage
and history.

22:34.000 --> 22:37.460
To be ignored
by it...

22:37.460 --> 22:38.830
It's an insult.

22:38.830 --> 22:40.880
Indeed.

22:40.880 --> 22:44.250
But one
that can be corrected.

22:44.250 --> 22:47.580
You are standing
on the edge

22:47.580 --> 22:52.000
of a great leap forward
for both my people and your own.

22:52.000 --> 22:56.000
You will be part of something
that has never occurred.

22:56.000 --> 22:59.000
A second,
manipulated Terrigenesis

22:59.000 --> 23:02.000
will change the course
of our combined histories,

23:02.000 --> 23:06.670
and your name will forever
be linked to that great moment.

23:06.670 --> 23:07.880
[ Door opens ]

23:10.790 --> 23:13.580
Please excuse me.

23:15.620 --> 23:16.880
♪♪

23:16.880 --> 23:20.250
We're having
some mechanical issues

23:20.250 --> 23:22.330
with both water and power
in the underground sectors.

23:22.330 --> 23:24.620
Where are
the maintenance crews?

23:24.620 --> 23:28.210
Conscripted into the Guard,
at your request.

23:28.210 --> 23:30.420
I fear this may be
the work of loyalists

23:30.420 --> 23:32.750
or even members
of the Royal Family themselves.

23:32.750 --> 23:34.790
There's no way
they've remained here.

23:34.790 --> 23:36.710
They've teleported back
to the safety of Earth.

23:36.710 --> 23:38.500
Perhaps.

23:38.500 --> 23:40.120
It could be sympathizers.

23:40.120 --> 23:43.000
Find the guards who used to be
on those crews and investigate,

23:43.000 --> 23:45.380
and tell them to remain there
on repair duty

23:45.380 --> 23:46.670
until further notice.

23:46.670 --> 23:48.750
♪♪

23:48.750 --> 23:50.880
Declan.

23:50.880 --> 23:52.790
[ Footsteps approach ]

23:52.790 --> 23:55.460
Please,
bring your case.

23:55.460 --> 24:00.580
♪♪

24:09.580 --> 24:12.170
[ Inhales deeply ]

24:12.170 --> 24:15.670
The parley
was worth a try.

24:15.670 --> 24:18.000
And I know that
it confirmed your worst fears.

24:18.000 --> 24:19.670
Do you remember
the first time

24:19.670 --> 24:21.670
that I came
into the Quiet Room?

24:21.670 --> 24:25.920
I came because I had heard what
you had done to your parents,

24:25.920 --> 24:27.580
and I wanted
to gloat.

24:27.580 --> 24:34.290
After the hurt
that they had caused me...

24:34.290 --> 24:35.790
I thought it was
a wonderful turn of events

24:35.790 --> 24:38.210
that now
you were suffering.

24:38.210 --> 24:42.460
I wanted
to see you in pain.

24:42.460 --> 24:44.580
I thought
that you were irredeemable.

24:44.580 --> 24:46.830
♪♪

24:46.830 --> 24:49.290
Okay, but then
you looked at me,

24:49.290 --> 24:52.210
and I saw it
in your face.

24:52.210 --> 24:54.580
I saw that we were
the same person.

24:54.580 --> 24:56.790
We just had
different circumstances.

24:56.790 --> 24:59.290
We were both caught up
in something

24:59.290 --> 25:03.460
that --
that we couldn't control,

25:03.460 --> 25:06.380
and -- and it
hurt us deeply.

25:06.380 --> 25:10.420
And that pain
allowed us to be friends.

25:10.420 --> 25:14.500
What I saw today
was very familiar.

25:14.500 --> 25:17.620
It was two people
with the same pain.

25:17.620 --> 25:20.120
♪♪

25:20.120 --> 25:22.830
Nothing is irredeemable.

25:22.830 --> 25:25.040
It's a lovely story.

25:25.040 --> 25:28.080
But it ignores
a larger truth.

25:28.080 --> 25:29.880
A context.

25:31.290 --> 25:33.500
Well...

25:33.500 --> 25:36.460
I'm sorry that
you feel this way, Karnak.

25:36.460 --> 25:39.290
We bear some responsibility
for everything that's happened.

25:39.290 --> 25:40.790
We can choose rightly,

25:40.790 --> 25:43.790
and I hope that we do
when the time comes.

25:44.830 --> 25:46.920
The queen...

25:46.920 --> 25:50.710
The queen
has her hopes.

25:50.710 --> 25:53.080
And so do I.

25:53.080 --> 25:56.290
If we are to win,
we need our captain.

25:56.290 --> 25:58.290
I reviewed
Declan's research,

25:58.290 --> 26:01.080
and there's a flaw in it,
of course.

26:01.080 --> 26:04.380
Let's let Maximus
figure that out on his own.

26:04.380 --> 26:07.040
But I have a fix,
and I want to use it

26:07.040 --> 26:10.830
to bring Gorgon back
through a second Terrigenesis.

26:10.830 --> 26:13.880
It's dangerous,
and I can't be sure it'll work.

26:13.880 --> 26:15.250
But what if --

26:15.250 --> 26:17.380
Medusa: This is not
the Karnak I know,

26:17.380 --> 26:19.210
the one who wouldn't dare
make a move

26:19.210 --> 26:21.790
unless he was certain
that he would win.

26:21.790 --> 26:23.960
I don't want
my hope to wither

26:23.960 --> 26:27.170
while I wait
on certainty.

26:27.170 --> 26:29.710
I need to go --
now.

26:29.710 --> 26:34.420
♪♪

26:34.420 --> 26:37.290
I'm sorry,
but you know it's forbidden.

26:37.290 --> 26:39.710
A second Terrigenesis --

26:39.710 --> 26:43.380
it can produce madness,
addiction, even death.

26:43.380 --> 26:46.380
Those are fairy tales,
passed down for generations.

26:46.380 --> 26:48.830
No one actually knows.

26:48.830 --> 26:58.790
♪♪

26:58.790 --> 27:08.670
♪♪

27:08.670 --> 27:14.500
♪♪

27:19.170 --> 27:23.670
♪♪

27:23.670 --> 27:25.210
Auran:
I thought we had

27:25.210 --> 27:27.790
a maintenance crew
meeting us here.

27:27.790 --> 27:32.330
We need to figure out what
is going on with the power grid.

27:32.330 --> 27:41.960
♪♪

27:41.960 --> 27:44.670
♪♪

27:44.670 --> 27:46.170
Don't!

27:46.170 --> 27:55.920
♪♪

27:55.920 --> 28:00.290
This is
kind of important.

28:00.290 --> 28:04.500
Let's get this right.

28:04.500 --> 28:07.330
Let's get it right.

28:07.330 --> 28:17.210
♪♪

28:17.210 --> 28:19.460
♪♪

28:19.460 --> 28:21.710
We need to figure out what
is going on with the power grid.

28:21.710 --> 28:31.580
♪♪

28:31.580 --> 28:33.380
Don't!

28:33.380 --> 28:41.960
♪♪

28:41.960 --> 28:44.750
I'm not gonna let you
kill me again.

28:44.750 --> 28:46.960
I'm here
to help you.
Who said
I need help?

28:46.960 --> 28:48.120
You know my power.

28:48.120 --> 28:49.960
I see the flaw
in everything.

28:49.960 --> 28:51.420
And exploit it.

28:51.420 --> 28:53.120
I see the flaw
in you.

28:53.120 --> 28:55.380
And I want to help you
overcome it.

28:55.380 --> 28:57.750
I saw you
across the courtyard today.

28:57.750 --> 29:02.710
I've been watching you closely
since Earth.

29:02.710 --> 29:05.290
You backed
the wrong man...

29:05.290 --> 29:07.000
and you know it.

29:07.000 --> 29:09.290
I know you feel regret
for Gorgon's death.

29:09.290 --> 29:11.120
His sacrifice
saved your life.

29:11.120 --> 29:12.710
That wasn't
his intention.

29:12.710 --> 29:15.620
What if it was?

29:15.620 --> 29:18.000
He could always
be counted on

29:18.000 --> 29:19.790
to do the right thing
at the right time,

29:19.790 --> 29:22.620
and he trained you
to be the same.

29:22.620 --> 29:26.710
But you are not there yet,
are you?

29:26.710 --> 29:27.960
♪♪

29:27.960 --> 29:30.250
Neither am I.

29:30.250 --> 29:32.170
The great Karnak...

29:32.170 --> 29:34.000
admitting to weakness?

29:34.000 --> 29:36.000
My time on Earth
changed me.

29:36.000 --> 29:37.120
Maybe.

29:37.120 --> 29:38.580
A little.

29:38.580 --> 29:40.580
♪♪

29:40.580 --> 29:44.290
I don't understand
how I can help.

29:44.290 --> 29:46.460
I'm gonna need
a bit of your DNA.

29:46.460 --> 29:52.540
♪♪

29:52.540 --> 29:54.790
Hey.

29:54.790 --> 29:56.880
How are you doing?

29:56.880 --> 29:58.960
Horrible.
Oh.

29:58.960 --> 30:01.380
What is it?
Tell me.

30:01.380 --> 30:02.580
Dave.

30:02.580 --> 30:06.750
I just left him without even
hardly saying goodbye.

30:06.750 --> 30:10.120
You really care about him,
don't you?

30:10.120 --> 30:12.460
Kind of.
[ Chuckles ]

30:12.460 --> 30:13.580
I guess.

30:13.580 --> 30:15.750
Even though
he's human?

30:15.750 --> 30:16.750
I know.

30:16.750 --> 30:18.830
It's so strange.

30:18.830 --> 30:21.620
I grew up
thinking they were so awful.

30:21.620 --> 30:22.880
Mm.

30:22.880 --> 30:24.830
But the truth is...

30:24.830 --> 30:27.580
they're not all bad,
are they?

30:27.580 --> 30:28.540
All I know is,

30:28.540 --> 30:30.460
I really want
to see him again.

30:30.460 --> 30:31.460
Yeah.

30:31.460 --> 30:33.580
I understand,
okay?

30:33.580 --> 30:37.000
You don't have a lot of friends
up here.

30:37.000 --> 30:39.040
When I was on Earth,
I would look out,

30:39.040 --> 30:42.210
and you know
what I saw?

30:42.210 --> 30:46.790
Just normal people,
living normal lives.

30:46.790 --> 30:51.460
No powers, no palaces --
just...lives.

30:51.460 --> 30:55.540
I think
that's what I want.

30:55.540 --> 30:57.790
With Dave?

30:57.790 --> 31:00.290
I want to have that choice,
at least.

31:00.290 --> 31:03.710
I won't settle.

31:03.710 --> 31:09.670
♪♪

31:09.670 --> 31:12.620
[ Rumbling, alarm blaring ]

31:12.620 --> 31:16.750
Your cousins
are sabotaging the city.

31:16.750 --> 31:18.120
Who's to say?

31:18.120 --> 31:20.580
Maybe Maximus
just underestimated

31:20.580 --> 31:23.710
what it takes to keep
a kingdom running smoothly.

31:23.710 --> 31:25.580
And maybe I'm talking
to the one

31:25.580 --> 31:28.120
who might know every crack in
that kingdom's infrastructure.

31:28.120 --> 31:30.830
That's possible.

31:30.830 --> 31:33.080
Now comes your part.

31:33.080 --> 31:34.080
Um...

31:34.080 --> 31:35.540
You're kidding.

31:35.540 --> 31:37.710
Captain of the Royal Guard's
afraid of needles.

31:37.710 --> 31:40.790
I thought that was the weakness
you were talking about.

31:40.790 --> 31:43.170
[ Inhales deeply ]

31:43.170 --> 31:53.120
♪♪

31:53.120 --> 31:54.380
♪♪

31:54.380 --> 31:56.540
Your regeneration powers
will adhere

31:56.540 --> 31:59.670
through the transfer process
using nanogene technology.

31:59.670 --> 32:09.580
♪♪

32:09.580 --> 32:17.330
♪♪

32:17.330 --> 32:19.170
There's something
you should know.

32:19.170 --> 32:23.710
My powers -- they may not be
so strong anymore.

32:23.710 --> 32:25.790
How do you mean?

32:25.790 --> 32:28.330
Something Declan said.

32:28.330 --> 32:30.750
Well, it was really
more of a warning,

32:30.750 --> 32:33.080
and I don't know
if it's true or not.

32:33.080 --> 32:37.380
But whatever makes me me
may not work the way it used to.

32:37.380 --> 32:42.170
♪♪

32:42.170 --> 32:44.420
I understand.

32:44.420 --> 32:48.120
I've had some -- some
difficulties of my own...

32:48.120 --> 32:51.540
which has forced me
to rethink.

32:51.540 --> 32:53.710
For the better,
maybe.

32:53.710 --> 32:56.500
Let's hope so.

32:56.500 --> 32:59.920
♪♪

32:59.920 --> 33:01.210
[ Crystals clattering ]

33:01.210 --> 33:02.750
[ Air whooshing ]

33:02.750 --> 33:10.880
♪♪

33:10.880 --> 33:12.710
You really think
this will work?

33:12.710 --> 33:15.330
♪♪

33:15.330 --> 33:17.380
[ Scoffs ]
I -- I need it to.

33:17.380 --> 33:18.710
That's all I know.

33:18.710 --> 33:28.210
♪♪

33:28.210 --> 33:37.580
♪♪

33:37.580 --> 33:44.880
♪♪

33:44.880 --> 33:46.040
Gorgon?

33:46.040 --> 33:49.710
♪♪

33:49.710 --> 33:51.880
Please. Please...

33:51.880 --> 33:53.710
This has to.

33:53.710 --> 33:56.330
♪♪

33:56.330 --> 33:57.500
Give it a second.

33:57.500 --> 33:59.040
Remember,
it takes time.

33:59.040 --> 34:09.120
♪♪

34:09.120 --> 34:11.120
♪♪

34:11.120 --> 34:15.000
It didn't.

34:15.000 --> 34:18.750
Maybe death
has a purpose.

34:18.750 --> 34:21.000
Maybe we're meant
to come to terms with that

34:21.000 --> 34:23.250
instead of trying to...

34:23.250 --> 34:26.420
avoid it.

34:26.420 --> 34:33.210
♪♪

34:33.210 --> 34:36.960
[ Guards shouting in distance ]

34:36.960 --> 34:39.420
Sounds like
a lot of people.

34:39.420 --> 34:41.120
We fight or flee.

34:41.120 --> 34:42.750
♪♪

34:42.750 --> 34:46.540
Flee, but I'm not fleeing
with you.

34:46.540 --> 34:54.290
♪♪

34:59.710 --> 35:06.250
♪♪

35:06.250 --> 35:08.960
Declan: This?

35:08.960 --> 35:10.620
This is it?
[ Chuckles ]

35:10.620 --> 35:12.380
Looks like
a phone booth.

35:12.380 --> 35:14.330
It's far more
than that.

35:14.330 --> 35:16.380
This is the key
to who we are.

35:16.380 --> 35:19.670
And we need
to get to it.

35:19.670 --> 35:20.540
Right.

35:21.830 --> 35:23.580
Okay.

35:23.580 --> 35:27.620
We've, um -- We've already
inserted the, uh, DNA in you,

35:27.620 --> 35:31.000
and we're sure about
the translational efficiency.

35:31.000 --> 35:33.210
So now we're just on to
the final phase.

35:34.250 --> 35:37.540
Into the booth,
then.

35:37.540 --> 35:39.880
Right.

35:44.540 --> 35:47.790
♪♪

35:47.790 --> 35:49.960
A Terrigen crystal.

35:49.960 --> 35:52.210
The missing piece?

35:52.210 --> 35:55.170
Oh.
What's it made of?

35:55.170 --> 35:56.620
You'll have
plenty of time

35:56.620 --> 36:00.000
to get acquainted
with the crystals later.

36:00.000 --> 36:01.750
Now...

36:01.750 --> 36:04.540
♪♪

36:04.540 --> 36:06.540
This isn't
how I imagined it.

36:06.540 --> 36:10.460
♪♪

36:10.460 --> 36:11.460
Sorry?

36:11.460 --> 36:14.330
Well,
before, when...

36:14.330 --> 36:18.380
when we went through
the first time...

36:18.380 --> 36:20.580
my family was here.

36:20.580 --> 36:22.750
My mother
and my father

36:22.750 --> 36:25.210
and my...brother.

36:25.210 --> 36:29.380
We were surrounded
by people who loved us.

36:29.380 --> 36:34.460
♪♪

36:34.460 --> 36:40.290
That feels like
a very, very long time ago.

36:40.290 --> 36:43.920
♪♪

36:43.920 --> 36:45.830
I wanted this
to be a victory.

36:45.830 --> 36:47.290
It is.

36:47.290 --> 36:48.790
It is.

36:48.790 --> 36:51.330
Like you said...

36:51.330 --> 36:56.210
the first
of a new generation.

36:56.210 --> 37:01.120
Right.

37:01.120 --> 37:02.750
♪♪

37:02.750 --> 37:05.420
On with it,
then.

37:05.420 --> 37:09.580
What the hell?

37:09.580 --> 37:11.580
Isn't that...?

37:11.580 --> 37:13.580
♪♪

37:13.580 --> 37:15.250
Gorgon.

37:15.250 --> 37:17.750
Declan: How did he
get in here?

37:17.750 --> 37:19.380
♪♪

37:19.380 --> 37:23.040
How, indeed.

37:23.040 --> 37:24.790
What is happening
inside my kingdom?

37:24.790 --> 37:25.790
[ Rumbling ]

37:25.790 --> 37:27.120
[ Alarm blaring ]

37:27.120 --> 37:28.580
That can't be good.

37:28.580 --> 37:32.170
Your Highness, there was
an incident in the control room.

37:32.170 --> 37:35.080
All surveillance is down.
We are completely blind.

37:35.080 --> 37:37.000
[ Rumbling ]

37:37.000 --> 37:39.830
Maximus:
Stay here.

37:39.830 --> 37:43.210
I'll return for you
once this is all cleared up.

37:43.210 --> 37:45.290
It's begun.

37:45.290 --> 37:51.500
♪♪

37:51.500 --> 37:53.580
[ Rumbling, crowd shouting ]

37:53.580 --> 37:55.420
♪♪

37:55.420 --> 37:57.080
Medusa: Triton,
is everything okay?

37:57.080 --> 37:58.500
Maximus is out
in the open.

37:58.500 --> 38:00.580
My guess -- they're taking him
back to his apartment.

38:00.580 --> 38:02.880
How many men
are with him?
Only six.

38:02.880 --> 38:04.080
[ Alarm continues ]

38:04.080 --> 38:05.250
You be careful.

38:05.250 --> 38:07.710
We just
got you back.

38:07.710 --> 38:09.880
♪ Nothin' ♪

38:09.880 --> 38:13.040
♪ Seems to kill me ♪

38:13.040 --> 38:14.580
Aah!

38:14.580 --> 38:20.620
♪ No matter how hard I try ♪
[ Grunts ]

38:20.620 --> 38:22.080
[ Woman screams ]

38:22.080 --> 38:27.250
♪ Nothin' is closin' my eyes ♪

38:27.250 --> 38:29.080
The cloak!

38:29.080 --> 38:33.880
♪ Nothing can beat me down ♪

38:33.880 --> 38:39.580
♪ For your pain or delight ♪

38:39.580 --> 38:41.500
♪♪

38:41.500 --> 38:45.710
♪ Give you everything I need ♪

38:45.710 --> 38:49.750
♪ Give you everything I own ♪

38:49.750 --> 38:55.000
♪ Give in if it could at least
be ours alone ♪

38:55.000 --> 38:56.790
♪ Alone ♪

38:56.790 --> 39:00.120
♪ Given everything I could ♪

39:00.120 --> 39:03.500
♪ Blow it to hell and gone ♪

39:03.500 --> 39:08.040
♪ Burrow down in
and then blow up the outside ♪

39:08.040 --> 39:12.170
♪ Blow up the outside ♪

39:12.170 --> 39:16.750
♪ Blow up the outside ♪

39:16.750 --> 39:21.210
♪ World ♪

39:21.210 --> 39:25.920
♪♪

39:25.920 --> 39:26.920
[ Knives clatter ]

39:26.920 --> 39:36.670
♪♪

39:36.670 --> 39:46.380
♪♪

39:46.380 --> 39:48.460
[ Grunts ]

39:48.460 --> 39:52.330
[ Alarm blaring in distance ]

39:52.330 --> 39:53.790
[ Grunts ]

39:53.790 --> 39:56.380
You're supposed to
be dead.

39:56.380 --> 39:59.040
[ Maximus grunts ]

39:59.040 --> 40:01.210
What is this?

40:01.210 --> 40:02.710
[ Groans ]

40:02.710 --> 40:04.420
♪♪

40:04.420 --> 40:09.670
You can't keep me locked up
in here like a prisoner!

40:09.670 --> 40:19.120
♪♪

40:19.120 --> 40:20.120
♪♪

40:20.120 --> 40:22.000
Alone at last.

40:22.000 --> 40:24.620
Brother
against brother.

40:24.620 --> 40:26.540
It's not like you
to hide in the dark.

40:26.540 --> 40:29.380
♪♪

40:29.380 --> 40:33.380
But I guess times change,
and us along with it.

40:33.380 --> 40:34.580
[ Grunts ]

40:34.580 --> 40:38.750
[ Coughs, laughing ]

40:38.750 --> 40:41.210
There's something
you might want to hear.

40:41.210 --> 40:44.290
Once I'd realized
that you were likely to attack,

40:44.290 --> 40:46.420
I enacted
a failsafe system.

40:46.420 --> 40:48.330
If I die,

40:48.330 --> 40:51.540
all of Attilan
dies with me.

40:51.540 --> 40:53.080
I enacted a measure

40:53.080 --> 40:55.880
that will destroy
our protective dome.

40:55.880 --> 40:59.380
And after that happens,
it'll only be a few seconds

40:59.380 --> 41:01.750
until we're all
turned into...

41:01.750 --> 41:02.540
space debris.

41:02.540 --> 41:03.790
[ Laughs ]

41:03.790 --> 41:05.380
And since
I'm the only one

41:05.380 --> 41:07.790
who knows how to keep this
from happening...

41:07.790 --> 41:11.380
it might be wise
to keep me alive.

41:11.380 --> 41:12.420
Or not.

41:12.420 --> 41:13.830
[ Chuckles ]

41:13.830 --> 41:15.790
It's your choice.

41:15.790 --> 41:19.710
[ Chuckling ]

41:19.710 --> 41:22.170
♪♪

41:30.540 --> 41:32.210
[ Electricity buzzing ]

41:32.210 --> 41:34.000
Oh, my kingdom for...

41:34.000 --> 41:37.080
an electron microscope.

41:37.080 --> 41:39.670
[ Generators whirring ]

41:41.290 --> 41:42.290
♪♪

41:42.290 --> 41:44.040
Okay.
All right.

41:44.040 --> 41:46.250
The lights have gone out.

41:46.250 --> 41:47.540
[ Crashing ]

41:47.540 --> 41:51.830
♪♪

41:51.830 --> 41:54.620
[ Man breathing heavily ]

41:54.620 --> 41:56.000
♪♪

41:56.000 --> 41:58.380
My name is Dr...

41:58.380 --> 42:01.920
Dr. Evan Declan,
and...

42:01.920 --> 42:04.540
I-I work for Maximus.

42:04.540 --> 42:07.580
I-I'm allowed
to be here.

42:07.580 --> 42:09.380
[ Growling ]

42:09.380 --> 42:17.120
♪♪

42:21.960 --> 42:31.960
♪♪

42:31.960 --> 42:41.960
♪♪

42:41.960 --> 42:50.250
♪♪
